text: Reagan Gomez-Preston (born April 24, 1980 in Detroit, Michigan) is an American television, voice, and movie actress. She is best known for playing Zaria Peterson, Robert and Jerri Peterson's oldest daughter on The WB sitcom The Parent 'Hood, which was her first acting role. She also makes the voice of Roberta Tubbs on The Cleveland Show. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American voice actors Category:Actors from Detroit
